@node "Introduction" "Einführung"

@{MS "Introduction"}

When snooping around in PD collections I noticed that I did not run programs
without a gadget user interface. Sometimes, when I did, then these big templates
were frustrating me.@{par}

This was the reason for creating "R". "R" generates an GUI for each program
using an original commodore template, when specifing the "?" option.@{par}

"R" is more than 12 years old and I found it a few days ago. Well there is still
no tool around that allows such feature, so I decided to update the manual and
reworked the program to handle the needs of the year 2005!@{par}

@endnode
@node "SystemRequirements" "System Requirements"

@{MS "System Requirements"}

    ° Kickstart 2.0 or bigger!

    ° OS2.0+!

@endnode
@node "FeatureList" "Features"

@{MS "Features"}

° Automatic creation of a high quality MUI GUI for most available commands.@{par}

° Automatically localizes any known argument item.@{par}

° Save and auto load of predefined command options.@{par}

° Optional auto use mode for commands you need more than once with nearly the
same option set.@{par}

° Very small and easy to use.@{par}

° Full locale support.@{par}

° Online help.@{par}

@endnode
