@node "Buglist" "Bug list"

@{MS "Bug list"}

@{MC "R is unable to find a command"}

It's currently not entirely possible to check if a command, that "R" should
create a GUI for, exists. In such cases a wrong GUI is displayed.@{par}

Since version 2.04 "R" tries to locate a command. If the command was not
found it reports an error and does not open any window.@{par}

This is only working for command attached to the c: drawer and commands in the
current dir. Most command paths are attached via assign to c: so this isn't a
problem. Some drawer are only attached to the console by the path command. This
for example is the system drawer. Trying to run "r format" won't work. "format
?" will.@{par}

To work around simply specify the entire path or move into the commands
directory when calling "R".@{par}

It's possible to deactivate the new command detection mechanism. After
deactivation all commands are found again, but if a command does not exist e.g.
"r dirr" a window for that not existing command will be opened.@{par}

@{MC "Exchange and other system tools are crashing R!"}

That's a problem related to these tools. Just try:@{par}

Exchange "@{par}

That's not an error. Just one "! Now AmigaDos is telling these tools the
argument the user specified was wrong and it crashing. It's not happening
everywhere, but be warned.@{par}

@endnode
