@node "MainMenuOpen" "The Main Window - Project/Open Profile..."
@toc "MainMenu"

@{MS "Open Profile..."}

This item allows to load a profile which contains all settings of the
@{"main window." link "MAST"}.@{par}

@{u}It's not possible and useful to load profiles from other commands, so it's
only possible to load a profile made with the same command or an command using
the same @{"template" link "FAQSTemplate"}.@{uu}@{par}

This option becomes handy when dealing with different configurations for the
same command.@{par}

@endnode
@node "MainMenuSaAs" "The Main Window - Project/Save Profile As..."
@toc "MainMenu"

@{MS "Save Profile As..."}

This menu item is opening a file request and after specifying a name the entire
set up of the @{"main window." link "MAST"}.@{par}

@{u}It's not possible and useful to load profiles from other commands, so it's
only possible to load a profile made with the same command or an command using
the same @{"template" link "FAQSTemplate"}.@{par}

@endnode
@node "MainMenuSaDe" "The Main Window - Project/Save Profile As Default"
@toc "MainMenu"

@{MS "Save Profile As Default"}

The entire set up of the @{"main window." link "MAST"} is stored on ENVARC:. If
you restart "R" with the same command these settings will be auto loaded.@{par}

If you prefer a temporary solution, then you should use the menu item
@{"Use As Default" link "MainMenuUsDe"}.@{par}

@endnode
@node "MainMenuUsDe" "The Main Window - Project/Use Profile As Default"
@toc "MainMenu"

@{MS "Use Profile As Default"}

The entire set up of the @{"main window." link "MAST"} is stored in ENV:.
If you restart "R" with the same command these settings will be auto
loaded.@{par}

The settings stay until reboot or system shut down. If you prefer a more
longterm solution, then you should use the menu item
@{"Save As Default" link "MainMenuSaDe"}.@{par}

@endnode
@node "MainMenuAbou" "The Main Window - Project/About..."
@toc "MainMenu"

@{MS "About..."}

By using this menu item you'll get a window containing information about the program and it's author.@{par}

@endnode
@node "MainMenuQuit" "The Main Window - Project/Quit"
@toc "MainMenu"

@{MS "Quit"}

Very easy! Quit quits "R"! (-8

@endnode
@node "MainMenuReDe" "The Main Window - Edit/Reset To Defaults"
@toc "MainMenu"

@{MS "Reset To Defaults"}

The entire window set up will be reset to "factory" defaults.@{par}

@endnode
@node "MainMenuLaSa" "The Main Window - Edit/Last Saved"
@toc "MainMenu"

@{MS "Last Saved"}

The last saved configuration will be loaded into the window.@{par}

@endnode
@node "MainMenuLaUs" "The Main Window - Edit/Restore"
@toc "MainMenu"

@{MS "Restore"}

The last temporary used configuration will be loaded into the window.@{par}

@endnode
@node "MainMenuGlob" "The Main Window - Edit/R Preferences"
@toc "MainMenu"

@{MS "R Preferences"}

This item simply opens the @{"R Preferences" link "GLOB"}!@{par}

@endnode

