@{"The Main Window" link "MAST"} @{"R Preferences" link "Glob"}

@endnode
@node "GLOBCHEC" "R Preferences - Command Check"
@toc "GLOB"

@{MS "Command Check"}

If this switch is set, "R" is checking if the specified command exists. If it
does not exist, then "R" reports an error.@{par}

This detection is not working with resident command or with commands not in the
path chain. If you experience any problem with the default setup, then the
command check can be disabled.@{par}

Please read also the @{"bug list" link "BUGLIST"} section.@{par}

@endnode
@node "GLOBKEYW" "R Preferences - Force Keywords"
@toc "GLOB"

@{MS "Force Keywords"}

Normally "R" is using all possible Keywords. This may cause the argument line to
be to big.@{par}

By turning this option off the created command line will be size optimized.@{par}

@endnode
@node "GLOBAUDE" "R Preferences - Automatic Defaults"
@toc "GLOB"

@{MS "Automatic Defaults"}

"Automatic defaults" force "R" to select the menu item
"@{"use as defaults" link "MainMenuUsDe"}" every time a command is executed.
If the same command is called again the last used profile will be automatic
loaded.@{par}

Without setting this option you can manually select the
"@{"use as defaults" link "MainMenuUsDe"}" menu item and store the
profile on your own.@{par}

@endnode
@node "GLOBLOCA" "R Preferences - Localize Keyword"
@toc "GLOB"

@{MS "Localize Keyword"}

Normally the AmigaDOS keywords are in english. "R" is able to translate many
known keywords into the system language.@{par}

Even if your system language is set to english, this localization is useful. "R"
is translating from the "Template"-language into a human language. Specifically
the english language provides more readable keywords by separating words and
changing their cases in a logic way. E.g. the "DIRS" will be translated into
"Directories"!@{par}

If - however - you dislike this feature you can turn it off by using this switch.@{par}

@{b}Changing this option requires a restart of "R" to make the changes active!@{ub}@{par}

@endnode
@node "GLOBLAMO" "R Preferences - Original Keyword"
@toc "GLOB"

@{MS "Original Keyword"}

When using the @{"localization feature" link "GLOBLOCA"} it might be helpful if the original keywords
are also shown.@{par}

@{b}Changing this option requires a restart of "R" to make the changes active!@{ub}@{par}

@endnode
@node "GLOBSHSA" "R Preferences - Show /A"
@toc "GLOB"

@{MS "Show /A"}

Some arguments must be specified to successfully execute a command. As an
example take a look on the "TO" argument of the "Copy"-Command.@{par}

To visualize these arguments "R" is displaying them bold. By turning on this option the keyword
will be also extended by "/A".@{par}

@{b}Changing this option requires a restart of "R" to make the changes active!@{ub}@{par}

@endnode
@node "GLOBSHSM" "R Preferences - Show /M"
@toc "GLOB"

@{MS "Show /M"}

Arguments which support multiple arguments can be optionally visualized by
appending a "/M".

@{b}Changing this option requires a restart of "R" to make the changes
active!@{ub}@{par}

@endnode
@node "GLOBSHSF" "R Preferences - Show /F"
@toc "GLOB"

@{MS "Show /F"}

When activated a final argument will be visualized by appending a "/F".@{par}

@{b}Since "R" is handing the arguments automatically this option is just for "I
want that option"-Freaks!@{ub}@{par}

@{b}Changing this option requires a restart of "R" to make the changes
active!@{ub}@{par}

@endnode
@node "GLOBSHSK" "R Preferences - Show /K"
@toc "GLOB"

@{MS "Show /K"}

When activated any keyword argument will be visualized by appending a "/K".@{par}

@{b}Since "R" is handing the arguments automatically this option is just for "I
want that option"-Freaks!@{ub}@{par}

@{b}Changing this option requires a restart of "R" to make the changes
active!@{ub}@{par}

@endnode
@node "GLOBSHSN" "R Preferences - Show /N"
@toc "GLOB"

@{MS "Show /N"}

When activated any numeric argument will be visualized by appending a "/N".@{par}

@{b}Changing this option requires a restart of "R" to make the changes
active!@{ub}@{par}

@endnode
@node "GLOBSHSS" "R Preferences - Show /S"
@toc "GLOB"

@{MS "Show /S"}

When activated any switch argument will be visualized by appending a "/S".@{par}

@{b}Since "R" arguments these into checkboxes this is just for "I want that
option"-Freaks!@{ub}@{par}

@{b}Changing this option requires a restart of "R" to make the changes
active!@{ub}@{par}

@endnode
@node "GLOBSHST" "R Preferences - Show /T"
@toc "GLOB"

@{MS "Show /T"}

Toggle arguments can be optional visualized by appending a "/T".@{par}

@{b}Changing this option requires a restart of "R" to make the changes
active!@{ub}@{par}

@endnode
@node "GLOBSAVE" "R Preferences - Save"
@toc "GLOB"

@{MS "Save"}

The setup made within the window will be save to disk.

@endnode
@node "GLOBOKOK" "R Preferences - Use"
@toc "GLOB"

@{MS "Use"}

The setup made within this window will be temporary saved in memory and lost
after reset or system shut down.@{par}

@endnode
@node "GLOBCANC" "R Preferences - Cancel"
@toc "GLOB"

@{MS "Cancel"}

Any changes to the setup will be lost and the window will be closed.@{par}

Closing the window has the same effect.@{par}

@endnode

@node "GLOBMenu" "R Preferences - Menu Overview"
@toc "GLOB"

@{MS "Menu Overview"}
@{code}
@{MS "Project"}
@{JCENTER}@{"Open..." link "GlobMenuOpen"}
@{"Save As..." link "GlobMenuSaAs"}
@{MS "Edit"}
@{JCENTER}@{"Reset To Defaults" link "GlobMenuReDe"}
@{"Last Saved" link "GlobMenuLaSa"}
@{"Restore" link "GlobMenuLaUs"}
@endnode
@node "GLOBMenuOpen" "R Preferences - Project/Open..."
@toc "GLOBMenu"

@{MS "Open..."}

This item allows to load any R-preferences file.@{par}

@endnode
@node "GLOBMenuSaAs" "R Preferences - Projekt/Save As..."
@toc "GLOBMenu"

@{MS "Save As..."}

This item allows to save the current settings into a selectable file.@{par}

@endnode
@node "GLOBMenuReDe" "R Preferences - Edit/Reset To Defaults"
@toc "GLOBMenu"

@{MS "Reset To Defaults"}

The entire window will be reset to "factory" defaults.@{par}

@endnode
@node "GLOBMenuLaSa" "R Preferences - Edit/Last Saved"
@toc "GLOBMenu"

@{MS "Last Saved"}

The last saved setup will be restored.@{par}

@endnode
@node "GLOBMenuLaUs" "R Preferences - Edit/Restore"
@toc "GLOBMenu"

@{MS "Restore"}

The last temporary setup will be restored.@{par}

@endnode
